briefdescription.para: Macro for creating and initializing a NFC NDEF record descriptor for a TENP Status Record.

detaileddescription.para: This macro creates and initializes an instance of type nfc_ndef_record_desc and an instance of type nfc_ndef_tnep_rec_status, which together constitute an instance of a TNEP status record.
Use the macro NFC_NDEF_TNEP_RECORD_DESC to access the NDEF TENP record descriptor instance. Use name to access a TNEP Status description.

parameterdescription.para: Name of the created record descriptor instance.
TNEP Message Status.

briefdescription.para: Macro for creating and initializing a NFC NDEF record descriptor for a TNEP Service Parameter Record.

detaileddescription.para: This macro creates and initializes an instance of type nfc_ndef_record_desc and an instance of type nfc_ndef_tnep_rec_svc_param, which together constitute an instance of a TNEP service parameter record.
Use the macro NFC_NDEF_TNEP_RECORD_DESC to access the NDEF TNEP record descriptor instance. Use name to access a TNEP Service Parameter description.

parameterdescription.para: Name of the created record descriptor instance.
TNEP Version.
Service name uri length in bytes.
Service name uri.
TNEP communication mode.
Minimum waiting time.
Maximum number of waiting time extensions.
Maximum NDEF message size in bytes.

briefdescription.para: Macro for accessing the NFC NDEF TNEP record descriptor instance that was created with NFC_NDEF_TNEP_RECORD_DESC.
Payload constructor for the NDEF TNEP Status Record.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the TNEP status record description.
Pointer to the payload destination. If NULL, function will calculate the expected size of the Text record payload.
Size of the available memory to write as input. Size of the generated record payload as output.
If the operation was successful. Otherwise, a (negative) error code is returned.
